# docker-compose/dev environment notes

# The current dev Docker setup script does not use this file as the runtime env file.
# This file is intentionally documentation-only to avoid maintaining a stale duplicate .env template
# under docker-compose/dev/.

# Runtime env files live in the project root:
#
#   .env.development  # default, local/test verification
#   .env.test         # optional test environment
#   .env.prod         # optional production environment
#
# Usage:
#
#   docker-compose/dev/setup.sh up --no-build
#   docker-compose/dev/setup.sh up --env development --no-build
#   docker-compose/dev/setup.sh up --env test --no-build
#   docker-compose/dev/setup.sh up --env prod --no-build
#
# Or select the env via environment variable:
#
#   NAIYUN_ENV=prod docker-compose/dev/setup.sh up --no-build

# The dev compose overrides these internal service values inside the lobe container:
#
#   DATABASE_URL -> compose PostgreSQL
#   REDIS_URL    -> compose Redis
#   SEARXNG_URL  -> compose SearXNG
#
# External MinIO / Casdoor / model / SMTP settings are read from the selected root env file.

# Required values should be maintained in the selected root env file:
#
#   APP_URL
#   AUTH_SECRET
#   KEY_VAULTS_SECRET
#   S3_ENDPOINT
#   S3_PUBLIC_DOMAIN
#   S3_BUCKET
#   S3_ACCESS_KEY_ID
#   S3_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY
#   AUTH_CASDOOR_ISSUER
#   AUTH_CASDOOR_ID
#   AUTH_CASDOOR_SECRET

# Notes:
#
# 1. Do not configure these deprecated LobeChat 2.0 variables, or the container will fail fast:
#      ACCESS_CODE
#      NEXT_AUTH_SECRET
#      NEXTAUTH_URL
#      NEXT_PUBLIC_SERVICE_MODE
#
# 2. The current dev compose no longer starts RustFS / MinIO. Do not duplicate local object-store
#    variables here.
#
# 3. For WeChat / Bot Gateway:
#      APP_URL          = browser/public callback URL
#      INTERNAL_APP_URL = container-internal callback URL, injected by docker-compose/dev/docker-compose.yml
